1
00:01:17,720 --> 00:01:18,840
Who made

2
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:21,520
such a mess?

3
00:01:37,640 --> 00:01:38,440
It's early morning.

4
00:01:38,440 --> 00:01:39,770
What are you doing here?

5
00:01:43,960 --> 00:01:45,720
Someone's dead!

6
00:01:47,600 --> 00:01:49,640
Someone's dead!

7
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:52,600
Over here.

8
00:01:52,600 --> 00:01:53,200
What happened?

9
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:54,860
It looks like someone is dead.

10
00:01:57,880 --> 00:01:59,600
Rigor mortis has spread throughout the body.

11
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:00,840
Livor mortis is fixed.

12
00:02:00,840 --> 00:02:02,970
Time of death was over eight hours ago.

13
00:02:09,840 --> 00:02:10,800
Before death,

14
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:13,520
the victim was likely struck on the head with a blunt object.

15
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:14,160
I checked.

16
00:02:14,160 --> 00:02:16,000
There are no footprints or other traces.

17
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:17,280
It's probably because of the rain.

18
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:18,810
It washed everything away.

19
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:22,920
It'll be hard to find witnesses.

20
00:02:22,920 --> 00:02:24,850
Who would go out in such heavy rain?

21
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:31,610
Look at this pit.

22
00:02:31,720 --> 00:02:33,980
The body must have been dug out from here.

23
00:02:35,160 --> 00:02:36,520
It's all spoiled food.

24
00:02:37,320 --> 00:02:38,280
That's strange.

25
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:40,000
Why did he bury these things?

26
00:02:40,079 --> 00:02:41,440
Director Cao was such a good man.

27
00:02:41,440 --> 00:02:42,900
Why would anyone kill him?

28
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:46,640
Take the body back first.

29
00:02:46,640 --> 00:02:48,240
The crowd is getting bigger.

30
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:51,840
The deceased is named Cao Mingli,

31
00:02:51,840 --> 00:02:53,840
the director of Guangren Hospital.

32
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:54,520
The body...

33
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:56,200
was found this morning during garbage collection

34
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:57,640
by a rickshaw puller.

35
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:00,530
The victim has been dead for over eight hours.

36
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:02,840
There is a lot of soil on the clothes,

37
00:03:02,920 --> 00:03:04,480
likely left when he was dug out

38
00:03:04,480 --> 00:03:05,410
from the ground.

39
00:03:05,680 --> 00:03:06,760
Except for the head,

40
00:03:06,760 --> 00:03:09,560
no other external injuries were found.

41
00:03:09,880 --> 00:03:10,740
We can conclude

42
00:03:10,840 --> 00:03:12,800
death was caused by a blunt force blow to the head,

43
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:14,530
resulting in a skull fracture.

44
00:03:15,960 --> 00:03:18,090
Only the head suffered severe trauma.

45
00:03:18,840 --> 00:03:19,720
That implies

46
00:03:19,720 --> 00:03:21,880
the victim was likely attacked

47
00:03:21,880 --> 00:03:23,010
while defenseless.

48
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:25,040
Has the primary crime scene been found?

49
00:03:25,040 --> 00:03:25,840
Not yet.

50
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:27,600
I asked around.

51
00:03:28,440 --> 00:03:29,880
He was last seen

52
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:31,520
at 4:00 PM.

53
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:32,840
But when he got off work,

54
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:33,720
no one noticed.

55
00:03:34,840 --> 00:03:36,000
I feel like

56
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:38,600
the primary crime scene must be near the hospital.

57
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:40,120
Otherwise, the killer would have no reason

58
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:41,240
to go through all the trouble

59
00:03:41,240 --> 00:03:43,840
of moving the body to the hospital's back alley.

60
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:44,900
I feel the same way.

61
00:03:45,360 --> 00:03:47,320
Then who dug him out?

62
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:51,560
The most important thing now

63
00:03:51,560 --> 00:03:53,490
is to find the primary crime scene.

64
00:03:53,560 --> 00:03:55,079
This is a laboratory.

65
00:03:55,480 --> 00:03:57,280
Up ahead is the nurse station.

66
00:03:57,560 --> 00:03:59,280
There's also a pharmacy here.

67
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:02,000
This is Director Cao's office.

68
00:04:02,920 --> 00:04:04,040
And the room next to it

69
00:04:04,040 --> 00:04:05,280
is the archives.

70
00:04:05,840 --> 00:04:07,900
All patient records are stored here.

71
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:08,760
On the second floor,

72
00:04:08,760 --> 00:04:09,880
there are wards

73
00:04:09,880 --> 00:04:11,240
and a dispensing room.

74
00:04:17,760 --> 00:04:19,560
Do you go in and out of these rooms

75
00:04:19,560 --> 00:04:20,839
at night?

76
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:22,570
Basically everywhere.

77
00:04:23,360 --> 00:04:25,090
Except the director's office.

78
00:04:31,840 --> 00:04:32,600
Bao.

79
00:04:33,520 --> 00:04:36,560
Lin Lan sent us to find the primary crime scene.

80
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:38,500
What are we doing here?

81
00:04:40,040 --> 00:04:41,760
It rained so hard last night.

82
00:04:42,240 --> 00:04:43,640
If the crime scene was outside,

83
00:04:43,640 --> 00:04:44,760
it would've been washed away.

84
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:45,890
Where would we look?

85
00:04:46,760 --> 00:04:47,620
Think about it.

86
00:04:48,400 --> 00:04:50,520
The killer buried the body

87
00:04:50,520 --> 00:04:52,320
because he didn't want it found.

88
00:04:52,440 --> 00:04:53,720
Now that it's dug up,

89
00:04:53,840 --> 00:04:55,040
he must be panicking.

90
00:04:55,360 --> 00:04:56,600
He definitely wants to know

91
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:58,400
how our investigation is going.

92
00:04:58,840 --> 00:05:01,040
He'll likely return to the crime scene.

93
00:05:01,880 --> 00:05:04,010
What if we catch the killer right here?

94
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:06,360
That's Bao for you.

95
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:09,200
You haven't lost your touch.

96
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:12,560
Bao.

97
00:05:23,640 --> 00:05:24,160
Stop running!

98
00:05:24,160 --> 00:05:24,800
Freeze!

99
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:25,920
Stop running!

100
00:05:26,200 --> 00:05:26,680
Freeze!

101
00:05:28,160 --> 00:05:28,720
Stop running!

102
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:29,400
Freeze!

103
00:05:30,560 --> 00:05:31,160
Freeze!

104
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:33,280
Stop running!

105
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:38,240
Lin Lan.

106
00:06:41,520 --> 00:06:44,050
Don't you think this spot is unusually clean?

107
00:06:49,400 --> 00:06:51,060
It looks like it's been wiped.

108
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:57,280
There's another spot here.

109
00:06:57,280 --> 00:06:59,409
Only these two places have been wiped.

110
00:07:03,960 --> 00:07:06,020
This must be the primary crime scene.

111
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:17,260
All the ornaments in this room are symmetrical,

112
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:19,890
except for this candlestick. One is missing.

113
00:07:20,280 --> 00:07:21,960
The murderer likely used this candlestick

114
00:07:21,960 --> 00:07:23,280
to kill the victim.

115
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:25,040
Then cleaned up the blood

116
00:07:25,200 --> 00:07:27,080
and buried the body in the backyard.

117
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:28,000
Don't run!

118
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:28,600
Don't run!

119
00:07:29,080 --> 00:07:29,680
Don't run!

120
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:34,480
Stop!

121
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:38,600
Stop!

122
00:07:50,920 --> 00:07:52,520
She's not from our hospital.

123
00:07:52,640 --> 00:07:54,600
She often rummages through the trash cans in the back alley.

124
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:56,000
I've run into her many times.

125
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:58,130
Yeah, I've run into her many times too.

126
00:08:02,280 --> 00:08:03,880
She doesn't have any wounds.

127
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:07,770
Where did this blood come from?

128
00:08:09,080 --> 00:08:10,640
Then these clothes probably aren't hers.

129
00:08:10,640 --> 00:08:12,570
She's not even from this hospital.

130
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:14,530
Where did she come from?

131
00:08:14,720 --> 00:08:15,160
Let go.

132
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:16,240
Let go.

133
00:08:16,840 --> 00:08:17,240
Let go.

134
00:08:18,720 --> 00:08:19,400
What are you doing?

135
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:20,600
Trying to grab my gun?

136
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:33,130
Take her back to the police station first.

137
00:08:33,679 --> 00:08:35,400
Based on the evidence collected so far,

138
00:08:35,400 --> 00:08:36,840
it's basically confirmed that

139
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:39,640
the killer struck in Director Cao's office.

140
00:08:40,039 --> 00:08:41,360
After the murder,

141
00:08:41,360 --> 00:08:43,760
they disguised Director Cao's body as a patient,

142
00:08:43,760 --> 00:08:44,880
transported it out of the hospital,

143
00:08:44,880 --> 00:08:46,610
and buried it in the back alley.

144
00:08:47,640 --> 00:08:49,240
I can't believe after all this investigation,

145
00:08:49,240 --> 00:08:50,120
the one digging up the body

146
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:51,650
turned out to be a madwoman.

147
00:08:52,720 --> 00:08:54,120
The patient gown she's wearing

148
00:08:54,120 --> 00:08:56,450
must have been stripped off Director Cao.

149
00:08:58,440 --> 00:08:59,920
To commit murder in the hospital

150
00:08:59,920 --> 00:09:02,080
and move the body unnoticed,

151
00:09:02,560 --> 00:09:04,920
the killer must be someone from the hospital.

152
00:09:04,920 --> 00:09:07,320
So the killer is either a doctor or a nurse.

153
00:09:07,760 --> 00:09:10,640
But we've taken statements from the doctors and nurses.

154
00:09:10,640 --> 00:09:12,640
They all have alibis.

155
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:14,360
Unless someone is lying.

156
00:09:14,520 --> 00:09:15,720
Could it be a patient?

157
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:18,000
Or a patient's family member?

158
00:09:19,520 --> 00:09:22,320
Whether it's a doctor, a patient, or a nurse,

159
00:09:22,400 --> 00:09:24,330
there has to be a motive for murder.

160
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:25,840
We need to check first

161
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:26,560
if Director Cao

162
00:09:26,560 --> 00:09:28,220
held a grudge against anyone.

163
00:09:28,280 --> 00:09:29,840
That crazy woman you brought back,

164
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:31,770
just let her go if there's no issue.

165
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:33,960
What's the deal with keeping her in my office?

166
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:34,640
She keeps looking at me

167
00:09:34,640 --> 00:09:36,200
and laughing "hehehe".

168
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:37,800
It gives me goosebumps.

169
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:45,320
Why don't we send her back to the hospital?

170
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:47,280
Stop her from digging through trash.

171
00:09:47,280 --> 00:09:49,440
Who knows what disease she might catch.

172
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:51,040
Forget about the hospital.

173
00:09:51,040 --> 00:09:52,500
It's like being in prison.

174
00:09:52,560 --> 00:09:53,320
Besides,

175
00:09:53,320 --> 00:09:55,250
she's used to being free out there.

176
00:09:55,480 --> 00:09:58,240
Who knows what'll happen if she goes to the hospital.

177
00:09:58,240 --> 00:09:59,840
But we can't just ignore her.

178
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:02,280
Do you have any other ideas?

179
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:15,800
Look,

180
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:17,800
she's actually quite cooperative.

181
00:10:17,840 --> 00:10:20,100
Ciyang Hall is a legitimate sanatorium.

182
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:22,250
It's safer than being outside.

183
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:28,160
I found it.

184
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:29,920
I have news.

185
00:10:31,040 --> 00:10:31,960
Last month,

186
00:10:32,040 --> 00:10:32,800
at Guangren Hospital,

187
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:34,720
a wealthy merchant from Suzhou died during treatment.

188
00:10:34,720 --> 00:10:35,680
The merchant's wife

189
00:10:35,680 --> 00:10:37,200
made a huge scene.

190
00:10:37,280 --> 00:10:37,960
The director

191
00:10:37,960 --> 00:10:39,960
spent a lot of money to hush it up.

192
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,520
You mean

193
00:10:42,520 --> 00:10:44,250
the family is seeking revenge?

194
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:45,520
That's not what I mean.

195
00:10:45,520 --> 00:10:47,600
I asked around at the hospital.

196
00:10:47,680 --> 00:10:49,400
They said the director was furious

197
00:10:49,400 --> 00:10:50,930
and ended up firing a nurse.

198
00:11:00,760 --> 00:11:02,090
Zhang Xiaojuan, right?

199
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:04,040
Central Police Station.

200
00:11:04,040 --> 00:11:04,680
Lin Lan.

201
00:11:06,160 --> 00:11:07,820
You were doing well as a nurse.

202
00:11:07,880 --> 00:11:09,280
Why become a taxi dancer?

203
00:11:09,520 --> 00:11:10,840
What's wrong with being a taxi dancer?

204
00:11:10,840 --> 00:11:12,040
Just making a living.

205
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:14,520
Are taxi dancers inferior?

206
00:11:14,520 --> 00:11:15,850
That's not what I meant.

207
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:17,420
I just wanted to ask

208
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:19,240
why you left the hospital.

209
00:11:19,240 --> 00:11:21,240
What mistake did you actually make?

210
00:11:21,560 --> 00:11:23,020
I didn't make any mistake.

211
00:11:26,560 --> 00:11:28,000
I'm just a scapegoat.

212
00:11:30,640 --> 00:11:32,560
I just followed Dr. Sun's prescription

213
00:11:32,560 --> 00:11:35,160
and gave the patient 0.1 of digitalis tincture.

214
00:11:35,160 --> 00:11:36,620
I didn't do anything else.

215
00:11:37,440 --> 00:11:39,520
He is the president of the Suzhou Chamber of Commerce.

216
00:11:39,520 --> 00:11:40,560
If his family

217
00:11:40,760 --> 00:11:42,320
wants to make a big fuss out of this,

218
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:44,320
I can kiss my job as the dean goodbye.

219
00:11:44,800 --> 00:11:46,040
Anyway, regarding this matter,

220
00:11:46,040 --> 00:11:47,170
someone must step up

221
00:11:47,800 --> 00:11:48,800
to take the blame.

222
00:11:52,480 --> 00:11:52,740
Ten.

223
00:11:57,040 --> 00:11:58,200
You mean

224
00:11:58,440 --> 00:11:59,700
it was Dr. Sun's fault?

225
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:01,200
I didn't say that.

226
00:12:02,280 --> 00:12:03,940
Dr. Sun has saved many people.

227
00:12:04,120 --> 00:12:06,180
I don't think it was her fault either.

228
00:12:06,640 --> 00:12:07,840
So it was an accident.

229
00:12:10,560 --> 00:12:11,800
Since it was an accident,

230
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:13,000
and Director Cao

231
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:14,440
made you a scapegoat,

232
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:16,060
don't you hate him?

233
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:17,040
I do.

234
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:22,260
But what's the use?

235
00:12:22,800 --> 00:12:23,860
He is the director.

236
00:12:24,240 --> 00:12:25,320
I am just a nurse.

237
00:12:25,520 --> 00:12:27,240
Did you ever think about revenge?

238
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:28,200
What do you mean?

239
00:12:28,840 --> 00:12:30,280
Between 4:00 PM yesterday

240
00:12:30,280 --> 00:12:31,760
and midnight,

241
00:12:32,040 --> 00:12:32,900
where were you?

242
00:12:34,120 --> 00:12:35,040
Officer,

243
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:36,360
if you have something to say,

244
00:12:36,360 --> 00:12:37,440
just say it.

245
00:12:37,520 --> 00:12:38,880
Director Cao is dead.

246
00:12:39,320 --> 00:12:40,560
Did you know that?

247
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:42,640
Director Cao is dead?

248
00:12:46,760 --> 00:12:47,240
Wait.

249
00:12:48,160 --> 00:12:49,800
You don't suspect me, do you?

250
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:51,000
I wouldn't go so far as to

251
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:52,960
kill for a job like that.

252
00:12:53,120 --> 00:12:55,250
You just need to answer our questions.

253
00:12:55,480 --> 00:12:56,540
Whether it was you,

254
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:57,840
we will find out.

255
00:13:01,640 --> 00:13:03,240
I got up at 4:00 PM yesterday.

256
00:13:03,640 --> 00:13:05,700
I washed up, had noodles downstairs,

257
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:07,240
went home to get ready,

258
00:13:07,240 --> 00:13:08,440
and then went to work.

259
00:13:08,640 --> 00:13:10,300
I didn't get off until 1:00 AM.

260
00:13:11,360 --> 00:13:12,960
If you don't believe me, Sir,

261
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:14,730
feel free to ask around.

262
00:13:23,960 --> 00:13:26,680
But Director Cao didn't offend anyone else.

263
00:13:27,720 --> 00:13:28,360
I still think

264
00:13:28,360 --> 00:13:30,880
the killer must be someone from the hospital.

265
00:13:30,880 --> 00:13:33,120
Otherwise, how could no one have noticed?

266
00:13:33,120 --> 00:13:35,240
The killer murdering Director Cao

267
00:13:35,840 --> 00:13:37,120
doesn't necessarily mean

268
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:38,760
they had a grudge against him.

269
00:13:38,760 --> 00:13:39,840
Is it possible

270
00:13:40,080 --> 00:13:42,080
he knew a secret he shouldn't have?

271
00:13:42,440 --> 00:13:43,400
Or maybe

272
00:13:43,720 --> 00:13:45,640
he had something on the killer?

273
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:48,480
Time to eat,

274
00:13:49,240 --> 00:13:50,520
detectives.

275
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:52,760
Put your work aside for now.

276
00:13:53,160 --> 00:13:54,240
Let's eat first.

277
00:13:55,880 --> 00:13:56,610
Look at this.

278
00:13:59,200 --> 00:14:00,320
Don't rush.

279
00:14:00,680 --> 00:14:02,280
I'll go to the hospital again tomorrow.

280
00:14:02,280 --> 00:14:04,920
I want to see what kind of monsters are there.

281
00:14:07,960 --> 00:14:08,720
Is that enough?

282
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:09,580
That's enough.

283
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:11,800
Here.

284
00:14:12,520 --> 00:14:12,880
Okay.

285
00:14:13,080 --> 00:14:14,800
Go to the hospital tomorrow.

286
00:14:14,800 --> 00:14:15,800
Spread the word

287
00:14:15,800 --> 00:14:17,600
that the killer has been caught.

288
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:19,320
Then proceed as planned.

289
00:14:19,880 --> 00:14:20,480
What plan?

290
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:27,720
Bao.

291
00:14:28,040 --> 00:14:29,600
These ribs smell amazing.

292
00:14:29,960 --> 00:14:31,200
Where did you buy this?

293
00:14:31,200 --> 00:14:32,200
What kind of question is that?

294
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:33,760
This is my secret recipe.

295
00:14:33,840 --> 00:14:35,300
You can't buy it anywhere.

296
00:14:35,560 --> 00:14:36,120
Here.

297
00:14:36,320 --> 00:14:36,880
Eat it while it's hot.

298
00:14:36,880 --> 00:14:37,640
Come on.

299
00:14:42,280 --> 00:14:43,000
Officers.

300
00:14:46,720 --> 00:14:47,400
Officers,

301
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:48,450
you're back.

302
00:14:50,400 --> 00:14:51,040
Yes.

303
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:52,800
Regarding President Cao's case,

304
00:14:52,800 --> 00:14:54,060
is there any progress?

305
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:55,440
You guessed it.

306
00:14:56,440 --> 00:14:57,840
We came here today

307
00:14:57,840 --> 00:14:59,440
mainly to inform everyone.

308
00:14:59,720 --> 00:15:01,080
The murderer of Dean Cao

309
00:15:01,560 --> 00:15:02,760
has been captured.

310
00:15:03,680 --> 00:15:04,280
Really?

311
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:05,720
That's great news.

312
00:15:05,720 --> 00:15:07,000
He's finally caught.

313
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:08,060
That's wonderful.

314
00:15:08,480 --> 00:15:09,160
Sir.

315
00:15:09,160 --> 00:15:10,440
Who is the killer?

316
00:15:14,520 --> 00:15:15,650
Regarding Dean Cao,

317
00:15:16,200 --> 00:15:17,800
we express our deep regrets.

318
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:19,520
Dean Cao's killer

319
00:15:20,080 --> 00:15:21,240
was actually a robber.

320
00:15:21,240 --> 00:15:21,880
What?

321
00:15:22,240 --> 00:15:23,800
How could it be a robber?

322
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:26,160
Dean Cao was such a good man.

323
00:15:26,160 --> 00:15:27,680
How could a robber do this?

324
00:15:27,680 --> 00:15:28,960
Exactly.

325
00:15:29,320 --> 00:15:30,680
What a shame.

326
00:15:44,640 --> 00:15:46,200
What kind of coffee is this?

327
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:47,200
It tastes awful.

328
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:48,930
You need to work on your skills.

329
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:52,280
How is Bao's medicine coming along?

330
00:15:52,280 --> 00:15:53,940
That is what you're drinking.

331
00:16:03,080 --> 00:16:04,680
Why didn't you say so sooner?

332
00:16:08,360 --> 00:16:10,240
I mixed it using Bao's ratio.

333
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:18,760
Miss Lin,

334
00:16:19,200 --> 00:16:20,640
what exactly did you eat?

335
00:16:20,680 --> 00:16:21,740
Why is it so severe?

336
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:24,960
She just drank a cup of overnight coffee.

337
00:16:26,760 --> 00:16:28,000
It's nothing serious.

338
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:30,600
You'll be fine after resting for a couple of days.

339
00:16:30,600 --> 00:16:31,800
If you don't want to stay in the hospital,

340
00:16:31,800 --> 00:16:32,760
you can go home.

341
00:16:35,120 --> 00:16:36,320
Forensic Expert Qin.

342
00:16:36,440 --> 00:16:37,160
Look,

343
00:16:37,160 --> 00:16:38,440
our department is so busy.

344
00:16:38,440 --> 00:16:40,100
Why don't you go back and help?

345
00:16:40,640 --> 00:16:42,640
The doctors here are looking after me anyway.

346
00:16:42,640 --> 00:16:43,970
You don't need to worry.

347
00:16:44,280 --> 00:16:44,800
True.

348
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:46,920
You seem to be fine.

349
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:49,440
I'll go back to work then.

350
00:16:49,680 --> 00:16:50,160
Go ahead.

351
00:16:50,160 --> 00:16:51,120
Get some rest.

352
00:16:56,240 --> 00:16:57,040
Dr. Sun,

353
00:16:57,440 --> 00:16:59,120
just let me be hospitalized.

354
00:16:59,120 --> 00:17:00,360
I just finished investigating a case,

355
00:17:00,360 --> 00:17:01,890
and I just want to rest well.

356
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:06,660
It's not easy for you guys.

357
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:07,480
Solving a case

358
00:17:07,480 --> 00:17:08,940
has worn you out like this.

359
00:17:10,640 --> 00:17:12,319
But regarding Director Cao,

360
00:17:12,319 --> 00:17:13,579
it's all thanks to you.

361
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:15,730
I never expected

362
00:17:15,920 --> 00:17:18,180
that Director Cao was killed by robbers.

363
00:17:18,560 --> 00:17:19,960
These days,

364
00:17:19,960 --> 00:17:21,319
it's not safe out there.

365
00:17:22,599 --> 00:17:23,800
When you go out,

366
00:17:23,800 --> 00:17:25,329
you need to be more careful.

367
00:17:27,839 --> 00:17:29,800
How was that kidnapper caught?

368
00:17:32,920 --> 00:17:33,680
Dr. Sun,

369
00:17:34,240 --> 00:17:36,570
are you also interested in solving cases?

370
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:37,960
Not really.

371
00:17:38,800 --> 00:17:40,800
Ever since Director Cao was killed,

372
00:17:41,280 --> 00:17:43,610
everyone in the hospital has been on edge.

373
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:45,320
It's fine.

374
00:17:45,320 --> 00:17:46,640
Don't worry too much.

375
00:17:47,080 --> 00:17:49,340
Cases like Director Cao's are isolated.

376
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:51,460
Besides, the killer has been caught.

377
00:17:52,160 --> 00:17:52,820
Just relax.

378
00:17:56,280 --> 00:17:57,680
Everything here is good.

379
00:17:57,720 --> 00:17:58,850
It just costs money.

380
00:17:59,080 --> 00:18:00,740
I've only been here a few days,

381
00:18:00,880 --> 00:18:02,940
and I've already emptied my pockets.

382
00:18:04,600 --> 00:18:06,480
Life is more important than money.

383
00:18:06,480 --> 00:18:07,680
If you lose your life,

384
00:18:07,760 --> 00:18:09,490
who's going to spend the money?

385
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:10,440
That's true.

386
00:18:11,600 --> 00:18:13,600
It's a good thing Dr. Sun treated me.

387
00:18:14,560 --> 00:18:15,890
Dr. Sun treated you too?

388
00:18:16,480 --> 00:18:17,000
You too?

389
00:18:18,120 --> 00:18:19,520
Then you're quite lucky.

390
00:18:20,840 --> 00:18:21,770
What do you mean?

391
00:18:21,840 --> 00:18:22,970
She's very skilled.

392
00:18:23,320 --> 00:18:24,000
Yes, she is.

393
00:18:24,520 --> 00:18:26,160
You want to make an appointment with her?

394
00:18:26,160 --> 00:18:27,640
But you need connections.

395
00:18:27,880 --> 00:18:29,320
If it weren't for Dr. Sun,

396
00:18:29,520 --> 00:18:31,280
I would have died twice already.

397
00:18:31,280 --> 00:18:32,680
Let me tell you,

398
00:18:32,760 --> 00:18:33,800
both times I fell ill,

399
00:18:33,800 --> 00:18:35,360
it was in the middle of the night.

400
00:18:35,360 --> 00:18:36,160
Thank goodness,

401
00:18:36,160 --> 00:18:37,200
Dr. Sun was there.

402
00:18:38,720 --> 00:18:39,880
Dr. Sun is here.

403
00:18:41,200 --> 00:18:42,920
Hello, Dr. Sun.

404
00:18:42,920 --> 00:18:43,720
Miss Lin,

405
00:18:44,520 --> 00:18:45,450
why are you here?

406
00:18:46,880 --> 00:18:48,680
I've been alone in the ward lately.

407
00:18:48,680 --> 00:18:49,880
It's too boring,

408
00:18:49,880 --> 00:18:52,000
so I wanted to come out for some fresh air.

409
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:53,520
In your condition, you need rest.

410
00:18:53,520 --> 00:18:54,640
You shouldn't be wandering around.

411
00:18:54,640 --> 00:18:56,320
If you're really bored,

412
00:18:56,320 --> 00:18:58,040
I'll have the nurse bring you some magazines.

413
00:18:58,040 --> 00:18:59,040
No need.

414
00:18:59,120 --> 00:19:00,200
I'll go back now.

415
00:19:00,760 --> 00:19:01,920
Thank you, Dr. Sun.

416
00:19:04,960 --> 00:19:07,640
Remember to check the temperature of the patient in Bed 3.

417
00:19:07,640 --> 00:19:08,200
Okay.

418
00:19:32,600 --> 00:19:33,240
Mr. Gu,

419
00:19:33,680 --> 00:19:35,800
the Commander sent us to extend his regards.
